258
00:24:29,572 --> 00:24:33,155
- Why don't you let her finish her drink first?
- Now, fucko!

259
00:24:35,578 --> 00:24:40,122
- Why you gotta talk to me like that, man?
- To her house.

260
00:24:40,208 --> 00:24:42,415
Come on, let's go.

261
00:25:14,785 --> 00:25:17,822
Rosie, I'm sorry. I fell asleep. Is Corinna OK?

262
00:25:19,415 --> 00:25:22,452
No, I'm coming home.
I'm coming home right now.

263
00:25:22,543 --> 00:25:24,619
OK.

264
00:25:30,510 --> 00:25:32,799
Oh, look who's up.

265
00:25:32,887 --> 00:25:34,963
Fuck off!

266
00:26:03,669 --> 00:26:05,377
Jimmy!

267
00:26:12,678 --> 00:26:14,754
Kilmartin.

268
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:34,731
Come in. I'll be off in a minute.

269
00:26:37,954 --> 00:26:40,659
Oh, Bev, no! Oh, no...

270
00:26:44,544 --> 00:26:47,664
She was a beautiful person, man.

271
00:26:48,965 --> 00:26:51,042
I did everything I could for her.

272
00:26:52,553 --> 00:26:54,629
I'm sorry.

273
00:26:55,472 --> 00:26:59,850
What was she doin' in your car
at eight in the morning, Ronnie?

274
00:27:00,894 --> 00:27:04,643
I sent her from the shop
to get somethin' from my house.

275
00:27:05,691 --> 00:27:08,811
- We were workin'...
- To get what?

276
00:27:13,115 --> 00:27:15,404
To get my wallet.

277
00:27:17,328 --> 00:27:19,700
To get your wallet?

278
00:27:24,502 --> 00:27:29,164
Jimmy, I swear, if that could be me in there...
I wouldn't have done it, man, cos I...

279
00:27:29,257 --> 00:27:31,333
- Let's go.
- We were workin'.

280
00:27:31,426 --> 00:27:34,593
- Wait a second. Wait.
- Let's go.

281
00:27:34,679 --> 00:27:37,004
Could Rosie bring Corinna to see me?

282
00:27:37,182 --> 00:27:40,800
- You know, it was you, drivin' that truck.
- Don't say that.

283
00:27:40,894 --> 00:27:43,599
Now I got nobody.

284
00:27:43,688 --> 00:27:46,262
Come on. Time to go.

285
00:27:49,486 --> 00:27:52,570
On the morning she died,
what time did Bev go to work?

286
00:27:52,656 --> 00:27:56,440
- I'm... not sure.
- Rosie, let me put it to you another way.

287
00:27:56,535 --> 00:28:00,615
What time did you come downstairs
so she could go to work? Six A.M.., seven A.M.?

288
00:28:00,706 --> 00:28:02,782
Ah, Jimmy...

289
00:28:08,589 --> 00:28:11,958
She never even made it home
from the night before.

290
00:28:14,053 --> 00:28:19,213
She called me from work, says
Ronnie's drivin' her, but she never made it.

291
00:28:19,308 --> 00:28:21,799
Jimmy, she never made it.

292
00:28:21,894 --> 00:28:25,643
- Ronnie.
- I was there all night. All night long.

293
00:28:25,732 --> 00:28:28,223
- Ronnie.
- Let's go.

294
00:28:30,945 --> 00:28:32,487
OK.

295
00:28:34,949 --> 00:28:39,030
- Your wallet, Ronnie? Your wallet?
- Come on!

296
00:28:39,955 --> 00:28:40,986
Come on!

297
00:28:41,081 --> 00:28:44,781
<i>- Now you're giving me names?
- You want 'em or not?</i>

298
00:28:44,876 --> 00:28:46,999
<i>What do you want? Early parole?</i>

299
00:28:47,087 --> 00:28:51,714
If I give people up to you and you turn me
loose early, I won't last day one out there.

300
00:28:51,800 --> 00:28:55,418
- So what do you want?
- I wanna visit my daughter.

301
00:28:58,599 --> 00:29:03,012
She's livin' upstate with my mother-in-law,
who won't let her come and see me.

302
00:29:03,103 --> 00:29:07,148
And I want a one-day trip
to go up there and see her. One day.

303
00:29:13,114 --> 00:29:16,031
- No.
- Whaddaya want from me?

304
00:29:17,535 --> 00:29:20,287
What do you mean? Like, in addition?

305
00:29:21,289 --> 00:29:23,780
Tell me something. Surprise me.

306
00:29:28,338 --> 00:29:30,793
Astro Jewelers. Remember that?

307
00:29:31,591 --> 00:29:34,426
- Four years ago.
- Mm-hm.

308
00:29:34,886 --> 00:29:37,638
I give you those people, I get my day.

309
00:29:40,308 --> 00:29:42,634
We'll see.

310
00:29:44,896 --> 00:29:47,103
John Amato. Call him Johnny A.

311
00:29:47,190 --> 00:29:50,026
And Bobby Bannion: Bobby B.

312
00:29:50,110 --> 00:29:52,731
They work at L&M Automotive
near Shea Stadium.

313
00:29:52,821 --> 00:29:55,822
- Anybody else?
- You should pick me up too.

314
00:29:55,908 --> 00:29:58,862
- Oh, yeah? Why's that?
- Well, if you don't...

315
00:29:58,952 --> 00:30:01,278
...they'll know who did the talking.

316
00:30:02,331 --> 00:30:05,202
So, throw me in a line-up.
I'll take my chances.

317
00:30:05,751 --> 00:30:08,325
That's all I have to say about this.

318
00:30:12,049 --> 00:30:15,252
Tell me about the navy yard.

319
00:30:16,596 --> 00:30:20,463
Same guys: Johnny A, Bobby B and me.

320
00:30:20,558 --> 00:30:24,176
That's three. There were four transporters.

321
00:30:28,483 --> 00:30:32,528
I didn't know the fourth driver.
I never saw him before.

322
00:30:32,612 --> 00:30:34,901
Who called you?

323
00:30:38,785 --> 00:30:42,035
Yo... Mr. Money.

324
00:30:44,291 --> 00:30:49,665
There is no way that you can tell me that you
did not know the guy who got you into this.

325
00:30:52,507 --> 00:30:55,045
Look me in the eye and try it.

326
00:30:58,889 --> 00:31:01,973
I've got no reason to lie.

327
00:31:04,478 --> 00:31:07,183
Everybody's got a reason to lie.

328
00:31:09,150 --> 00:31:11,985
Astro Jewelers? That was four years ago.

329
00:31:12,069 --> 00:31:14,477
Who ratted us out?

330
00:31:14,572 --> 00:31:17,526
Well, whoever it was, you're in the clear.

331
00:31:17,617 --> 00:31:22,160
I was the driver. The guy never laid eyes
on me. Did they pick Ronnie up too?

332
00:31:23,706 --> 00:31:27,075
- Ronnie Gannon?
- Yeah. The whole job was his idea.

333
00:31:27,168 --> 00:31:30,205
No, his name didn't even come up.

334
00:31:30,296 --> 00:31:33,582
Did the prosecutor's office
contact you about this?

335
00:31:33,675 --> 00:31:37,673
No. How stupid do ya think I am?
I wouldn't talk to anybody without you.

336
00:31:40,307 --> 00:31:44,684
Yeah. Well, they also got picked up
on the navy yard thing.

337
00:31:44,769 --> 00:31:47,687
- Who did?
- Bobby and Johnny.

338
00:31:48,398 --> 00:31:50,687
Ronnie too?

339
00:31:53,612 --> 00:31:57,479
- Ronnie Gannon...
- I never liked that kid.

340
00:31:57,574 --> 00:32:00,528
He's a fuckin' rat, is what you're sayin'.

341
00:32:00,619 --> 00:32:05,661
You gonna take care of this,
Junior, or are you goin' outta house?

342
00:32:06,417 --> 00:32:08,990
I clean up my own mess.

343
00:32:41,328 --> 00:32:44,198
- You ever see a Rolls get chopped?
- No.

344
00:32:44,289 --> 00:32:47,160
Why don't you stay and check it out?

345
00:32:49,211 --> 00:32:52,627
Come on, man.
I'm dyin' over here. Let's go!

346
00:32:55,884 --> 00:33:01,923
We ain't got all day, man. Let's go, man.
It ain't rocket science. Let's get outta here!

347
00:33:05,978 --> 00:33:10,272
Let's go to work. Let's get it up!

348
00:33:12,234 --> 00:33:14,310
Yo, Ronnie!

349
00:33:14,403 --> 00:33:17,238
Ronnie! Come here!

350
00:33:36,259 --> 00:33:40,423
What the fuck?
You guys look like the Gorton's fishermen.

351
00:33:43,308 --> 00:33:45,633
Ronnie, I want you to listen to this.

352
00:33:45,727 --> 00:33:48,598
An oldie but goodie.

353
00:33:48,689 --> 00:33:51,559
Concentrate on the words.

354
00:34:01,952 --> 00:34:04,277
Did ya hear that?

355
00:34:04,371 --> 00:34:07,206
Yeah. The bass was too heavy, though.

356
00:34:10,211 --> 00:34:14,789
"The time has come for everyone
to clean up their own back yard."

357
00:34:18,427 --> 00:34:21,879
"Clean up their own back yard."

358
00:34:22,515 --> 00:34:24,175
Did you hear that?

359
00:34:24,267 --> 00:34:27,434
Wait! What'd I do?

360
00:34:27,520 --> 00:34:29,596
I didn't do nothin'! What'd I do?

361
00:34:32,108 --> 00:34:35,857
You got somethin' to say?
You like to talk to the cops, huh?

362
00:34:35,945 --> 00:34:38,021
Huh?

363
00:34:38,657 --> 00:34:42,026
You like to fuckin' talk, you fuck? You fuck!

364
00:34:59,762 --> 00:35:01,635
Shit, Junior.

365
00:35:01,722 --> 00:35:03,845
- Shit.
- Ow.

366
00:35:06,393 --> 00:35:08,469
I like this. I really do.

367
00:35:16,862 --> 00:35:19,899
Ah, man, look at this. I just bought this thing.

368
00:35:34,005 --> 00:35:36,330
Let's get him outta here.

369
00:35:55,652 --> 00:35:59,401
- Kilmartin. On a day pass.
- Change your clothes in the cage.

370
00:36:07,873 --> 00:36:11,040
Mr. Kilmartin. We meet again.

371
00:36:12,253 --> 00:36:15,373
You remember old Calvin Hart here, don't ya?

372
00:36:20,052 --> 00:36:22,128
He sure as shit remembers you.

373
00:37:00,469 --> 00:37:02,758
Take the cuffs off him.

374
00:37:09,812 --> 00:37:11,888
Took the same bullet as you.

375
00:37:47,184 --> 00:37:49,675
Can I see my daughter now?

376
00:38:15,713 --> 00:38:17,871
- Hi.
- What happened to your face?

377
00:38:17,965 --> 00:38:21,833
Nothin'. Listen,
I don't think this is such a good idea.

378
00:38:21,928 --> 00:38:24,253
I don't want her to see me like this.

379
00:38:24,847 --> 00:38:27,255
Oh, Jimmy, she's a baby. She don't...

380
00:38:36,609 --> 00:38:39,776
- She ask for Bev a lot?
- In and out.

381
00:38:39,863 --> 00:38:43,528
Between me and Bev's mom,
she's doin' better than you think.

382
00:38:43,617 --> 00:38:48,029
I've been takin' her to classes with me.
She likes psych and economics.

383
00:38:48,121 --> 00:38:50,197
Math...

384
00:38:50,749 --> 00:38:54,996
That's great. I don't know
what I'd do without you, Rosie.

385
00:39:07,266 --> 00:39:09,342
Corinna.

386
00:39:18,778 --> 00:39:20,106
Hey.

387
00:39:20,196 --> 00:39:22,817
Hey, you! Hey.

388
00:39:25,118 --> 00:39:28,284
Hey, you, come here.
Corinna, do you know who I am?

389
00:39:28,371 --> 00:39:30,660
Just for one minute.

390
00:39:33,042 --> 00:39:35,118
I know.

391
00:39:36,629 --> 00:39:38,706
Ma-ma-ma...

392
00:39:41,301 --> 00:39:43,377
OK. All right.

393
00:39:50,769 --> 00:39:53,141
Don't take her away from me.

394
00:40:13,417 --> 00:40:16,087
Daddy, it stinks in here.

395
00:40:17,004 --> 00:40:19,376
It smells like soup!

396
00:40:22,009 --> 00:40:24,465
Soup, huh?

397
00:40:24,554 --> 00:40:26,630
Three more weeks.

398
00:40:26,723 --> 00:40:29,510
Hang in there, kiddo.

399
00:40:29,601 --> 00:40:31,427
Yeah...

400
00:40:31,519 --> 00:40:34,639
Comin' out to what? No job, no money...

401
00:40:36,191 --> 00:40:39,061
Least I got you, Juicy, right? Yeah.

402
00:40:39,611 --> 00:40:42,647
I wanna get your parents somethin'
for getting my apartment back.

403
00:40:42,739 --> 00:40:46,025
- And you got me.
- Whaddaya mean, I got you?

404
00:41:01,467 --> 00:41:03,009
Give it up!

405
00:41:03,093 --> 00:41:06,794
Kilmartin, report to the five building bypass.

406
00:41:06,889 --> 00:41:08,716
Kilmartin!

407
00:41:31,331 --> 00:41:33,407
Come on in.

408
00:41:46,888 --> 00:41:50,838
I hear you're comin' up
for parole review next week.

409
00:41:50,934 --> 00:41:54,019
I also hear you've been a pretty good guy.
That's great.

410
00:41:54,104 --> 00:41:56,180
Whaddaya want?

411
00:41:58,025 --> 00:42:03,019
Did you ever hear of an asshole
by the name of Little Junior Brown?

412
00:42:08,827 --> 00:42:10,904
Think.

413
00:42:11,622 --> 00:42:13,247
What about him?

414
00:42:16,836 --> 00:42:18,496
Little Junior...

415
00:42:18,588 --> 00:42:21,624
His old man, Big Junior?

416
00:42:21,716 --> 00:42:24,421
He's in the hospital. He ain't comin' out.

417
00:42:25,178 --> 00:42:28,760
So it looks like Little Junior's
movin' up in the world.

418
00:42:30,892 --> 00:42:32,968
Big Junior.

419
00:42:33,061 --> 00:42:37,059
That's one of those expressions like...
jumbo shrimp.

420
00:42:37,857 --> 00:42:39,933
Huh?

421
00:42:43,113 --> 00:42:45,355
Listen to me.

422
00:42:45,448 --> 00:42:49,612
I am not goin' back to that.
I am not rattin' on anybody else.

423
00:42:49,703 --> 00:42:52,455
What's done is done.
You can't make me do shit.

424
00:42:52,539 --> 00:42:55,624
We never swung the hammer on you
for the Astro job.

425
00:42:55,709 --> 00:42:58,995
Get the indictment on me.
Look, all I got to say to you...

426
00:42:59,087 --> 00:43:03,132
...is how you already cooperated with us
ratting out the others...

427
00:43:03,217 --> 00:43:07,345
...and here we are droppin' it on you anyhow
because you won't do any more ratting.

428
00:43:07,429 --> 00:43:09,920
You know what? You're right.

429
00:43:10,015 --> 00:43:13,598
Forget it.
We probably won't get the indictment.

430
00:43:15,187 --> 00:43:17,725
And you'll be out on the street.

431
00:43:19,233 --> 00:43:21,807
A free man.

432
00:43:21,903 --> 00:43:26,066
How long do you think you're gonna
last out there once the word gets out?

433
00:43:32,372 --> 00:43:34,448
Are you a man of honor?

434
00:43:35,959 --> 00:43:38,035
Sure.

435
00:43:38,712 --> 00:43:40,788
See, let me tell you.

436
00:43:41,673 --> 00:43:48,672
All I want now is what I had in my life
before all the fuckers came through the door -

437
00:43:48,764 --> 00:43:50,840
you and them.

438
00:43:51,683 --> 00:43:56,226
I wanna be left alone with my family,
and I want a job that feels good to me.

439
00:43:56,313 --> 00:44:00,145
So if that means I need to deliver up
this Junior Brown, I'll do that.

440
00:44:00,234 --> 00:44:03,817
If I have to kill this motherfucker to get there,
I will.

441
00:44:03,904 --> 00:44:06,360
But all I've got on you is your word.

442
00:44:06,448 --> 00:44:09,366
So I'm asking you: if I serve him up...

443
00:44:10,786 --> 00:44:17,204
...as a man of honor, will you say to me now
that you will cut me loose once and for all?

444
00:44:18,544 --> 00:44:20,620
Absolutely.

445
00:44:21,714 --> 00:44:24,501
D'you want my hand on it or something?

446
00:44:38,898 --> 00:44:40,974
OK, let him pass.

447
00:44:55,791 --> 00:44:57,867
James Kilmartin.

448
00:44:57,960 --> 00:45:00,332
- Rose D'Amico.
- Here.

449
00:45:00,963 --> 00:45:03,288
That's my daddy!

450
00:45:05,175 --> 00:45:07,251
Let's go.

451
00:45:21,943 --> 00:45:24,019
- Daddy, look!
- Hey, Corinna!

452
00:45:25,696 --> 00:45:29,113
What the hell's the matter with you?!

453
00:45:31,661 --> 00:45:34,413
The car almost hit me, Daddy.

454
00:45:34,497 --> 00:45:36,573
I know.

455
00:45:46,927 --> 00:45:50,509
- What the fuck is your problem, man?
- My father's dead!

456
00:45:50,847 --> 00:45:52,923
My father's dead!

457
00:45:54,434 --> 00:45:56,890
Come on, get it out. Come on.

458
00:46:00,858 --> 00:46:02,103
Argh!

459
00:46:37,103 --> 00:46:39,594
See the brother here with Junior?

460
00:46:39,689 --> 00:46:44,351
His name's Omar. Now, Omar's down
with some posse outta Philadelphia.

461
00:46:44,444 --> 00:46:49,023
Must got cash as long as train smoke
cos he's Junior's biggest customer.

462
00:46:49,116 --> 00:46:53,861
Cars, drugs, guns. He's buyin'
everything he can get his hands on.

463
00:46:54,496 --> 00:46:59,407
So when you hook up with your scumbag
pals, I want you to get 'em talkin' about Omar.

464
00:46:59,501 --> 00:47:03,084
He must be new. The Philadelphia PD
ain't got no jacket on him yet.

465
00:47:03,172 --> 00:47:05,248
Wait.

466
00:47:05,966 --> 00:47:08,837
Fuck this guy Omar. You said Little Junior.

467
00:47:08,928 --> 00:47:11,216
<i>This is about Little Junior.</i>

468
00:47:12,348 --> 00:47:17,888
Look, like if you get in some conversations,
just relax. Don't push for nothin', all right?

469
00:47:17,979 --> 00:47:22,973
Guy starts talkin', just ask for more details,
but nice and natural.

470
00:47:23,067 --> 00:47:25,143
Two assholes talkin' shop.

471
00:47:25,236 --> 00:47:30,479
But don't push, all right?
And don't initiate nothin', all right?

472
00:47:33,912 --> 00:47:37,031
Yeah, you gonna be fine. Just fine.

473
00:47:38,124 --> 00:47:40,794
Look, we in this together, man.

474
00:47:40,877 --> 00:47:43,249
One for all, all for one, right?

475
00:47:52,055 --> 00:47:54,427
OK, slow down. Slow.

476
00:47:57,769 --> 00:48:00,724
There it is. There. The Lexus, right there.

477
00:49:11,387 --> 00:49:15,135
I hate dogs! Little dogs, big dogs...

478
00:49:15,224 --> 00:49:17,300
Let's get outta here.

479
00:49:41,251 --> 00:49:43,658
